Text: The goals I had for this week was to integrate my C# portion with the rest of the team and allow interaction between API and the HTML, and a secondary goal was to test run my code to see if the expected response is given.
The interaction occurring on my end with HTML was perfect since this was facilitated with by serializing into a secondary JSon file for Indu to read and populate the interface.

However the interaction between the API has not been done yet, this should be a rather simple step since I will just need to adjust the code slightly from reading a Json file to calling on a method instead.
The response from parsing has been successful, however the additional function of removing the notification of read announcements has made it unecessarily complex.
Since previously whenever the my code was run it would overwrite the previous file that was passed to HTML meaning that whatever was displayed would always be stuff that needed to be shown.

But because of the read function the file needs to be saved meaning that i would have to perform multiple additional checks such as :  if the id of previous messaged matched new incoming messages and whether if the message itself was older than a week.

Over all i can say that development was doing good, whenever i was implementing the code the errors were easily debugged and the outcome where always close to or exactly what the expected outcome was.
However i had difficulty with the workflow and research.
For workflow there were sometimes changes with the specification of my application that resulted in me researching on something previously and putting in alot of time just for it to be made null.
For research itself it mainly came down to the incorrect methods used, as it was resulted in an implementation cycle where the result is vastly different from what was wanted.
If i were to face these problems again I would definitely read more before implementing the code, as i normally jump head first with coding just to back pedal to the starting point.
As for the workflow I would check with team for correct implementation or check which implementation is more simple.
I can say for certain that I am proud with how the code worked since there was no testing done previously, and and that all the research was done correctly.
The Goals I have for next week is to finish off the response portion of my code and start working on the presentation, as well as doing some tests to see if the newsfeed would actually be used or not
